description: This column is about the unique identifier for each delivery record within the e-commerce or online retail system. It is used to distinguish one delivery from another and is likely an auto-incrementing integer or a unique alphanumeric code.
This column is about storing the unique identifier for each order placed in the e-commerce or online retail system. Each 'id' value is distinct and helps in differentiating one order from another.
This column is about the name of the cardholder as it appears on the credit or debit card used for placing an order in the e-commerce system.

This column is about storing sensitive credit card information used for processing payments in an e-commerce or online retail system. It may contain the full credit card number or other related payment details.
This column is about the expiration date of the credit card used for placing an order. It indicates the month and year after which the card will no longer be valid for transactions.

This column is about the CVV (Card Verification Value) of a user's credit or debit card, which is a security feature typically consisting of a 3 or 4-digit number printed on the card. This value is required to complete online transactions and helps verify that the user has the physical card in their possession.
This column contains the street address where the customer's order will be delivered in an e-commerce or online retail system.
This column stores the name of the city where the userâ€™s order will be delivered. It is part of the shipping address information in the e-commerce or online retail system.

This column is about representing the state or region where the user's delivery address is located. It is used to specify the geographical area for shipping and billing purposes within the context of an e-commerce or online retail system.
This column contains the ZIP code of the address to which the order will be delivered. It is used to identify the postal region for delivery purposes.

This column is about storing the last four digits of a credit or debit card used for a transaction. It is used to help identify and verify the card without storing the full card number, thereby enhancing security.

This column is about storing the unique identifier for each product in the e-commerce or online retail system. It is likely an integer or GUID (Globally Unique Identifier) that uniquely distinguishes one product from another within the 'Product' table.

This column contains the names of the products available in the e-commerce or online retail system. Each entry in this column represents the specific name or title of a product that users can browse, select, and order for delivery.
This column stores the URL of the image associated with each product in the e-commerce or online retail system. It is used to display the product's image on the platform.

description: This column contains textual information about the products available in the e-commerce system. It provides detailed descriptions including features, specifications, and any other relevant details that help users understand the product better before making a purchase.
This column is about a unique identifier for each user in the e-commerce or online retail system's database. It is typically a numeric or alphanumeric value that distinguishes one user from another.
This column contains the names of users in an e-commerce or online retail system, where users can place orders for products and have them delivered.
